This paper deals with reducing the computational and memory requirements of neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the efficacy of pruning and quantisation techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the reduction of parameters in a network, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS).
